The title of our lecture\nis forms of making.
We think that making\nis fundamental to how
we operate as HANNAH.
From the ground up, digital\ndesign and fabrication
technologies are intrinsic\nto the making of our work,
facilitating fundamentally\nnew material methods,
tectonic articulations,\nenvironmental practices,
technological affordances,\nand forms of construction.
As architectural designers,\neight years out of school
and we're now\nlicensed, we consider
ourselves to be\nbiased generalists
rather than specialists.
The various projects\npresented in this lecture
combine a variety of\nmethods and material,
